## Final Verdict: Best White Gold Pear Diamond Ring for Every Budget

**Under $4,000 (complete ring):** 1ct lab pear (F-VS1, IGI Ideal) in the [Twisted Halo Diamond Engagement Ring](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings/design-your-own-ring/twisted-halo-diamond-engagement-ring-in-14k-white-gold-1-3-ct-tw-item-194983?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) in 14k white gold ([$1,955](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings/design-your-own-ring/twisted-halo-diamond-engagement-ring-in-14k-white-gold-1-3-ct-tw-item-194983?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) / 197 reviews). The lab pear at F-VS1 costs approximately $900–$1,400. Total ring: $2,900–$3,400.

This is the most compelling complete white gold pear ring on Blue Nile at this budget — 197 verified reviews on the setting, F-color lab stone that reads colorless against the cool metal, and a halo that adds perceived size to the pear silhouette. The Colorless Clarity Premium shrinks to near zero for lab buyers.

**$5,000–$8,000:** 1ct natural pear (G-VS2, GIA Ideal) in the [Pear Sidestone Diamond Engagement Ring](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings/design-your-own-ring/pear-sidestone-diamond-engagement-ring-in-14k-white-gold-1-4-ct-tw-item-192876?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) in 14k white gold ([$1,820](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings/design-your-own-ring/pear-sidestone-diamond-engagement-ring-in-14k-white-gold-1-4-ct-tw-item-192876?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) / 63 reviews). G is the cost-optimized color grade for natural pear diamonds in white gold — one grade below the optimal F but meaningfully cheaper, and detectable only under careful observation. The pear-specific basket proportions and V-prong placement are the strongest arguments for this setting at approximately $4,600–$5,300 total.

**$8,000–$16,000:** 1.5ct natural pear (F-VS2, GIA Ideal) in the [Pavé Diamond Halo Cathedral Engagement Ring](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings/design-your-own-ring/pave-diamond-halo-cathedral-engagement-ring-in-14k-white-gold-by-james-allen-item-315675?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) in 14k white gold ([$2,220](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings/design-your-own-ring/pave-diamond-halo-cathedral-engagement-ring-in-14k-white-gold-by-james-allen-item-315675?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) / 102 reviews). The Colorless Clarity Premium at 1.5ct is significant — but this is the budget tier where buyers who have decided to purchase F color are making that choice with clear purpose. In white gold with a 1.5ct F pear, the Colorless Clarity Premium is fully justified by the visual result — total approximately $13,000–$16,000.

**$18,000+:** 2ct natural pear (F-VS1, GIA Ideal) in the [Graduated Diamond Halo Engagement Ring by James Allen](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings/design-your-own-ring/graduated-diamond-halo-engagement-ring-in-14k-white-gold-by-james-allen-item-305007?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) in 14k white gold ([$2,985](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings/design-your-own-ring/graduated-diamond-halo-engagement-ring-in-14k-white-gold-by-james-allen-item-305007?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) / 99 reviews). At 2ct F-VS1, this is a genuinely exceptional pear diamond. White gold is the only metal that returns full value on a D–F purchase at this carat weight — warm metals mask the colorless quality you paid $10,000+ to achieve.

Total: approximately $20,000–$33,000. Consider platinum at this budget tier — the prong security and zero-maintenance advantages are most valuable on a ring of this significance.

